The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | BA special return fare to London 
                                                                                                               BA special return fare to London 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, March 5: British Airways today announced a special return fare to London of Rs 9,990, which, with taxes and surcharges, could work out to over Rs 31,000.        
	The offer, which covers limited seats, is for travel only till April 12 and bookings must be made by March 22. Average fares on the route are Rs 40,000 to Rs 45,000.        
	While the basic fare of Rs 9,990 was announced by the airline, travel agents said taxes and surcharges added up to around Rs 21,700. The special offer is available on the BA website, too.        
	India is an important market for us and we will continue to provide our customers value for money and service that they have come to expect from us, said BA commercial manager (South Asia) Amanda Amos.        
	The airline operates 48 flights from London to six cities in India. It operates flights twice daily from Mumbai and Delhi, every day from Bangalore, five times a week from Chennai and Hyderabad, and thrice a week from Calcutta.                                                                                                                                                                           
